 <div class="home-resources">
  <h4> Resources</h4>
 </div>
 <div class="home-description">
  <p>The lithologic patterns used in this application were derived from FDGC's 
     digital cartographic standard and compiled/converted into SVG format by the 
     University of Otago's geology department.  The Geologic Time Interval database
     table used in this application is based off of JSON data distributed by 
     the Paleobiology Database's Data Service 1.2 v2.  This application makes use of
     the PBDB's single taxa web services to provide additional fossil information.
     The Puerto Rico Geologic Map overlay used in the map API comes from the USGS's WMS Service.
     
  </p>
